text: Miller County is a county located in the southwestern corner of the U.S. state of Arkansas. As of the 2020 census, the population was 42,600. The county seat is Texarkana. == References == Category:1820 establishments in Arkansas Territory Category:1830s disestablishments Category:19th-century disestablishments in the United States Category:1870s establishments in Arkansas Category:1874 establishments in the United States
